The paper deals with the analysis of online algorithms for different online problems, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of relative worst order analysis and the introduction of list factoring as a supplementary proof technique suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of online algorithms. The use of list factoring as a proof technique may also suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT) due to its analysis of competitive algorithms.
